> A honey-based sauce may sound like something that goes with dessert, but mild-tasting pork loves a sweet sauce too, especially one that has a few savory elements added to the mix. We recommend spooning it on the roasted potatoes and side of green beans, too!

== Roasted Potatoes ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pork and Broccoli ==

While potatoes roast, pat @pork filet{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and mince half the @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Once pork is browned, transfer to one side of a second baking sheet.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Toss with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt and pepper on opposite side of baking sheet from pork.

Transfer sheet with pork and broccoli to middle rack; roast until pork is cooked through and broccoli is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Once pork is done, transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Thinly slice crosswise.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Honey Thyme Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add minced garlic and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Simmer, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until sauce has reduced and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash or two of water.

== To Serve ==

Divide pork, broccoli, and potatoes between plates. Drizzle pork with sauce and serve.